  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nTo support users with compromised withdrawal credentials there's a push to have a pre-approved list of `BlsToExecutionChange`s in op pools prior to the fork. This would be opt-in and voluntary, but if adopted by enough stakers could be very effective.\r\n\r\nThe format of the pre-approved data *should* be the same as the [POST request format for BLS to execution changes](https://ethereum.github.io/beacon-APIs/?urls.primaryName=dev#/Beacon/submitPoolBLSToExecutionChange), namely a JSON list of `SignedBlsToExecutionChange`. Even if we don't implement a CLI flag, users would still have the option to POST the file to their own node.\r\n\r\nThe CLI flag would just be a convenience:\r\n\r\n```\r\nlighthouse bn --preload-address-changes address_changes.json\r\n```\r\n\r\nRelated:\r\n\r\n- EIP-4736: https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-4736. The file formats defined here are outdated. The [latest video from CLWP](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EWkGyorgpAg) suggests that BLS to execution change messages will be provided.",
